text:
We stayed at the Swisse Belcourt on our return trip from Rote Island. To get a sea view we booked a twin room (Rp 482 800) as queen rooms were booked out. We got a discount by joining up and then used the Book Direct and Save. Also got a second drink free with a voucher sent with the booking confirmation.

The reception staff members were always friendly. After check in we were shown to the nearby lift which was under maintenance, so a couple of male staff were then asked to assist us with carrying our bags up the 2 flights of stairs. We never saw any work being done on the lift but we were only there for one day… Might want to check if you have any mobility issues. 

The room itself was sweltering hot but eventually the a/c did it’s job. The room itself was nice but the bedding had seen better days (some stains but seemed clean) and the twin beds were a little narrow. No safe either. The only bathroom facilities were 2 toothbrush packs. There wasn’t any soap for the sink but easy enough to reach the pump shower gel in the shower. The shower was cold even after running it for some time. The view was lovely though. 

The real stand out of the Swisse Belcourt is not the guest rooms but the main public areas. The view from the lobby bar area is great and the lobby area and foyers are decorated flamboyantly. This and the price of the room boosted my rating from a 3 to a 4. 

One suggestion I’d have is to let the guests know at check in that there are QR codes for the hotel information and for in room dining on the bedside table. I didn’t notice what these were until I was taking photos on the way out. Also, not much information was provided to guests e.g. we didn’t know that there is an inhouse restaurant downstairs until we had breakfast so had gone next door for dinner.
title: Great views - good price
